H.B. 974
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Apr 10, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH10433-MG-40A
Short Title: DHHS Study/Hospice Patient Complaints. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative G. Pierce.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT DIRECTING THE DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES TO
3 CONDUCT A STUDY ON WAYS TO ENCOURAGE GREATER ACCOUNTABILITY
4 BY HOSPICE CARE FACILITIES FOR COMPLAINTS BY HOSPICE CARE PATIENTS
5 AND THEIR FAMILIES.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7 SECTION 1. The Department of Health and Human Services shall conduct a study
8 to examine ways to improve the responsiveness of hospice care facilities to complaints by hospice
9 care patients and their families. In conducting this study, the Department shall analyze complaint
10 data collected from hospice care facilities, hospice care patients, and families of hospice care
11 patients. In addition, the Department shall engage stakeholders, including hospice care
12 administrators and representatives of North Carolina associations supporting hospice care
13 facilities such as the Association for Home and Hospice Care of North Carolina. The Department
14 shall report its findings and recommendations, including any legislative or administrative
15 proposals, to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on Health and Human Services and the
16 Fiscal Research Division by April 1, 2026. The report shall include, at a minimum, a summary
17 of the most common complaints by hospice care patients and their families and recommendations
18 on best practices for hospice care facilities to implement clear and accessible patient complaint
19 procedures, ensure timely and thorough investigations of patient complaints, foster open and
20 effective communication with hospice care patients and their families regarding patient
21 complaints, and empower families as active members of the care team.
22 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law.
*DRH10433-MG-40A*

